    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1587598428" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1587598428" />
    <a title="Jane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43273641-jane"><img alt="Jane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1564121970p2/43273641.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1587598428?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jane" href="/user/show/43273641-jane">Jane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780380708895" href="/book/show/580847.Merlin">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1587598428" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13816954828282547659"><b>An epic, amazing read.</b> I loved every moment of it, and was <b>drawn into the story from the very start.</b><br/><br/><b>Merlin/Myrddin is a great main character, so real, so believable, and so relateable</b>. His struggles, pain and trials are perfectly written, and how he responds is--agh, <b>just so good.</b><br/><br/><b>The Pendragon Cycle is the most epic Arthurian retelling ever. No arguments.</b> It is so very real, and amazing and I can totally see every single part happening. <b>Every page kept me hooked, reading...a little later at nigh</b></span>
  <span id="freeText13816954828282547659" style="display:none"><b>An epic, amazing read.</b> I loved every moment of it, and was <b>drawn into the story from the very start.</b><br /><br /><b>Merlin/Myrddin is a great main character, so real, so believable, and so relateable</b>. His struggles, pain and trials are perfectly written, and how he responds is--agh, <b>just so good.</b><br /><br /><b>The Pendragon Cycle is the most epic Arthurian retelling ever. No arguments.</b> It is so very real, and amazing and I can totally see every single part happening. <b>Every page kept me hooked, reading...a little later at night than I probably should have, just so I could finish.</b><br />There are epic battles and slow-motion-fighting that is <b>just totally cool</b>, and action everywhere.<br /><br /><b>I completely recommend this to all</b> (well, probably 13+). <b>An epic read</b>, and I can't wait for Arthur to properly come in.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13816954828282547659" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


