<span id="freeTextContainer2800645800641818568">I couldn&apos;t finish this book. I tried because I usually like to at least see what the ending entails but this book was so dry and repetitive that I could not finish it even if someone paid me. The story was slow and uneventful and the idea of Merlin being a Christian missionary didnt make any sense. He would even make comments about the the druids and how the last Celts needed to conform to the new God and Jesu. He didnt even practice a spiritual druidic life and was mostly vanishing and reappear</span>
  <span id="freeText2800645800641818568" style="display:none">I couldn't finish this book. I tried because I usually like to at least see what the ending entails but this book was so dry and repetitive that I could not finish it even if someone paid me. The story was slow and uneventful and the idea of Merlin being a Christian missionary didnt make any sense. He would even make comments about the the druids and how the last Celts needed to conform to the new God and Jesu. He didnt even practice a spiritual druidic life and was mostly vanishing and reappearing throughout his life and traveling Britian to see old friends. If you are looking for a retelling of the Arthurian legend, this is not it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2800645800641818568" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
