        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3521807377" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18427887684111844533">This book was exciting and entertaining, and I LOVE the historical fiction aspect. <br/><br/>As with book 1 in the series, I bought this book twenty years ago, put it on my bookshelf, moved a couple of times, put it in a box, and never read it. I can&apos;t even find the right book cover for this review. I went through a Merlin and Arthur phase, wrote reports in college about the Fisher King, and was way into all things mythology, read a bunch of books, but just never got to these.<br/><br/>This book covers all the base</span>
  <span id="freeText18427887684111844533" style="display:none">This book was exciting and entertaining, and I LOVE the historical fiction aspect. <br /><br />As with book 1 in the series, I bought this book twenty years ago, put it on my bookshelf, moved a couple of times, put it in a box, and never read it. I can't even find the right book cover for this review. I went through a Merlin and Arthur phase, wrote reports in college about the Fisher King, and was way into all things mythology, read a bunch of books, but just never got to these.<br /><br />This book covers all the bases, but I was less than enthralled by the heavy reliance on mysticism and scenes that reminded me of Greek choruses. I understand the reasoning and the relevance to this type of work. But compared to book 1, this one pales. I felt like it could have been half the length by cutting filler. <br /><br />After all this time, I will definitely look into book 3, but I hope it less resembles this book than the previous one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18427887684111844533" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


