<span id="freeTextContainer16433070499629515324"><strong>I could not put it down.</strong><br/><br/>Because the author writes as if speaking to the reader, the reader (myself) felt invited, included, and at time even questioned on whether or not this idea was worth the time and energy to consider. I am so drawn into the story that I feel I have a voice on who I want for king. Ect. <br/>I can&apos;t wait to read the next book or should I say I can&apos;t wait for the author to come and visit our world again.</span>
  <span id="freeText16433070499629515324" style="display:none"><strong>I could not put it down.</strong><br /><br />Because the author writes as if speaking to the reader, the reader (myself) felt invited, included, and at time even questioned on whether or not this idea was worth the time and energy to consider. I am so drawn into the story that I feel I have a voice on who I want for king. Ect. <br />I can't wait to read the next book or should I say I can't wait for the author to come and visit our world again.</span>
